The paper deals with graph drawing, which is a subfield of computational geometry (cs.CG). It specifically focuses on trees, which are a fundamental data structure in computer science and are often studied in the context of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The concept of ply-disks and ply-number is related to graph theory and combinatorics (cs.GT, cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses the area requirements of the drawings, which is a topic in computational complexity and computational optimization (cs.SI).
